functions.label: formatHit
description:
Returns a formatted document in form of key/value pairs of the fields name and a formatted value.
The value returned in each pair is an HTML string which is safe to be applied to the DOM, since
it's formatted using field formatters.

functions.label: getDocId
description:
Returning a generated id of a given ES document, since `_id` can be the same
when using different indices and shard routing

functions.label: getIgnoredReason
description:
Returns the reason why a specific field was ignored in the response.
Will return undefined if the field had no ignored values in it.
This implementation will make some assumptions based on specific types
of ignored values can only happen with specific field types in Elasticsearch.

children.label: field
description: Either the data view field or the string name of it.

children.label: ignoredFields
description: The hit._ignored value of the hit to validate.

functions.label: getShouldShowFieldHandler
description:
Returns a function for checking whether we should display a field in the Documents column of the data table
If showMultiFields is set to false, it filters out multifields that have a parent, to prevent entries for multifields
like this: field, field.keyword, field.whatever
